 <p>
In accordance to the Personal Data Protection Act 2012 (“PDPA”) in UK, sharing or transferring personal data refers to personal data of an individual who can be identified (a) from that data; or (b) from that data and other information to which the organisation has or is likely to have access. Pseudonymised data will not be treated as personal data provided VDB Group puts in place measures to prevent reidentification. To align with the global data protection legislations, VDB shall put in strict measures and treat such pseudonymised data as equivalent to personal data so long as such data cannot be reidentified. The sharing, transferring or publicly disclosing of such deidentified data will not require separate notification to you and your consent.
</p>
<br><br><h2>5. HOW DO WE STORE AND PROTECT YOUR DATA</h2>
<p>
We will only retain your information for as long as is necessary for providing VDB Services to you and will not hold or process your information for any longer than we are legally required to.
</p>
<p>
We established a comprehensive information security management system and access control and will take reasonable and practicable security measures and technical means to store and protect your personal information in accordance with industry standards to prevent the loss, unauthorised access, public disclosure, use, modification, destruction, loss or leakage of your information consistent with applicable data protection and privacy laws and regulations. Notwithstanding the foregoing, we may retain your information for up to 7 years to ensure that any contractual disputes can be addressed. We will take all reasonably practicable steps to protect your personal information.
</p>

